<br>
Note, I'm not disagreeing with the other part (about Nagafen).  That position is irefutable, you ARE 100% correct.  There was, therefore, absolutely no point in quoting or discussing that part (other than a reference to agreeing with you).<br>
<br>
However, I strongly doubt that even 1 Ragefire a week is wasted... and if wasted, I also strongly doubt that the existance of a FG reservation caused that... <br>
<br>
Time of spawn perhaps adds up to that, but I don't believe that the six FG reservations made each week have ever caused Ragefire to sit untouched... as Cralgar himself points out in the first post of this thread 4/5 of the FG reservations are veiled Ragefire reservations.  The exception recently has been my FG reservations... and Rage HAS NOT been up... therefore, nothing was wasted due to reservation.<br>
<br>
I also agree with Ryklith that the reservation system changed which cleric got an epic this weekend, while disagreeing with Kraghack that had FCFS been in place it certainly would have worked out only one other possible way.  However, that doesn't mean Ragefire was wasted, and it doesn't mean that the FG's caused a bottleneck... <br>
<br>
Note, I AM for working something out regarding Ragefire.  I AM of the belief that once thats worked out FG raids HAVE to subordinate to Ragefire just as they do to Nagafen.  I just have stopped trying to defend the validity of FG reservations and have chosen to attack the premise hoping to see some actual progress.<br>
<br>
The overriding problem with Cleric Epics are twofold.  One which you've pointed out Nagafen not being killed promptly (which causes far more waste than FG's) and the other situation that Watchers has noted (that right now the Fire Giant raid takes supremecy to the Ragefire camp... which is wrong).<br>
<br>
I'm open for solutions and compromise that address the actual problem... I'm just tired of Fire Giant raids being listed as the entire problem... they are a symptom of the problem, and at best a minor one.<br>
