<br>
Exactly Cralgar, that's the problem.  That's what people should be focusing on.  That is the reason a good third of the 'NO' votes on the FG reservations were made (read through the votes if its still out there, there are a lot of 'NO' stricticly because of Ragefire, NOT because of the reservation issue).  <br>
<br>
This is the thing that needs to be looked at, THIS is where a 'standard' needs to be set...  once set, I suspect that FG reservations will dwindle down to the three to five honest raids a month that occur... which means the reservations on FG's wont effect most peoples lives... ever... but will still allow those who wish to do the raid a chance to have the raid work out... that's win/win.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> <br>
My suggestion: Ragefire camper holds precedence over Fire Giant Raid... for the Nagafen room only.  Ragefire campers should NOT enter to Rage/Naggy lair &lt;8 hours before a scheduled raid out of courtesy for that raid... unless Rage is up (tracking) and then that guild/cleric should be courteous enough to contact the reservation guild to let them know to reschedule... considering there will only be three to five FG reservations it shouldn't be that tough to do.<br>
<br>
Further - Anyone scheduling a FG/Ragefire reservation is welcome to... however, only the FG's up to Naggy's lair are 'protected'.  They run a very firm chance that upon zoning in an established FCFS camp will be IN PLACE in Naggy's lair (or a monk feigning or whatever).  They can do their FG raid, and, if NO ONE IS CAMPING RAGE, may establish the Ragefire camp.  However, if Ragefire is camped actively, then even if Rage spawns they MUST wait out the campers raid (they may finish their FG raid up to the door to Naggy's lair).<br>
</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
I can state that as someone who reserves FG's for FG's, I'd sacrifice the last three spawns every now and then to respect a Ragefire FCFS.  Something like that clearly provides FCFS on Ragefire, sets a standard for precedence in camping, establishes an expected protocol for taking up a Rage camp when FG's are scheduled (do it +8 hours before their scheduled raid), removes any claim the FG/Rage reservations has, and still allows the actual FG raids to coexist on the rare occaisions they occur.<br>
