<br>
This weekend, a precedent was set.  The precedent is that a FG reservations counts as a ragefire reservation.<br>
<br>
I'm all for legitimate FG raids.  I want the 35-50 crowd to still be able to reserve FG's.  What I'm vehemently against, is 50+ people reserving FG's to farm them, or to try and reserve ragefire.  I'm also against legitimate FG raids preventing access to ragefire.<br>
<br>
I encourage any cleric that's camping ragefire to completely ignore any reservation on FG's made by a 50+ group attempting a Ragefire reservation.  I encourage a cleric camping Ragefire to work out a compromise with any legitimate FG raid that might be in the way of taking out Ragefire by either having them reschedule, or assisting them in starting their raid earlier.<br>
<br>
Letting people to continue to abuse the spirit of FG raids will eventually lead to the abolishment of scheduled FG raids altogether.  Respect legitimate FG raids.  Refuse to acknowledge illegitimate ones. <p><img src="http://www.pangea.ca/~grinch/sadune.jpg" width="400" height="175"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ukulanaesoulsease.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kulanae Soulsease</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Protector of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 461<br> <font color=#CC9900>(6/5/01 3:23:58 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.wwa.com/~danas/Kulanae5.gif height=158 width=119></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Hmm FG´s :)</span><hr size=1> Adun.....can we then expect the MOD's to meet and amend the rules regarding FG reservations?<br>
